13. What is a Multi-Branch Pipeline?

EXPLAIN IN THIS ANSWER:-
â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”â”
ğŸ‘‰ "A Jenkins Multi-Branch Pipeline automatically discovers, creates, and manages branches in a source control repository 
    (like GitHub, GitLab, or Bitbucket), ensuring feature branches are tested before merging into main. 
ğŸ‘‰ This approach eliminates manual job creation, speeds up development, and improves code quality."

âœ” Use Case: Useful for feature branches, pull requests, and different environments (dev/stage/prod).
âœ” Benefit: Automates CI/CD for multiple branches without creating separate jobs for each.

âœ… How Multi-Branch Pipeline Works?
1ï¸âƒ£ Jenkins scans the repository and detects new branches automatically.
2ï¸âƒ£ For each branch with a Jenkinsfile, Jenkins creates a separate pipeline dynamically.
3ï¸âƒ£ When a branch is deleted from Git, Jenkins automatically removes it from Jenkins UI.
